00:44:43,114 --> 00:44:45,990
♫ <i>I think of you</i>

719
00:44:48,953 --> 00:44:50,620
<i>(Bartholomew-Strydom) So that was it.</i>

720
00:44:50,663 --> 00:44:53,498
<i>I'd come to the point,</i>
<i>it was the end of the story.</i>

721
00:44:53,624 --> 00:44:57,585
<i>I was searching for a dead man.</i>
<i>One morning I discovered a living man.</i>

722
00:44:57,628 --> 00:45:00,630
And to me that was the end of the story.
I wrote my article,

723
00:45:00,673 --> 00:45:03,091
I called it ''Looking for Jesus.''

724
00:45:03,134 --> 00:45:04,634
I faxed it to many individuals,

725
00:45:04,760 --> 00:45:05,802
many people involved,

726
00:45:05,970 --> 00:45:10,640
but somehow this article
made its way across the Atlantic

727
00:45:10,766 --> 00:45:13,101
and into the hands
of someone in America.

728
00:45:13,144 --> 00:45:15,937
And what I thought was the end of story

729
00:45:15,980 --> 00:45:18,648
was actually just the beginning
of another story,

730
00:45:18,691 --> 00:45:21,317
and the best part was still to come.

731
00:45:23,612 --> 00:45:26,156
'Cause I don't know where it is.
It might take a while.

732
00:45:26,198 --> 00:45:28,283
They do have the dates.

733
00:45:28,325 --> 00:45:31,202
''Three-year search for dead singer.''
Yes.

734
00:45:31,328 --> 00:45:34,622
August '97. I was in Kansas.

735
00:45:34,665 --> 00:45:38,501
I got a copy of it to me at work.
I was on, like, a 24-hour shift.

736
00:45:38,627 --> 00:45:40,837
And then, I went online

737
00:45:41,005 --> 00:45:45,175
and that's when
I discovered the website.

738
00:45:45,301 --> 00:45:49,053
When I went online there was
this milk carton with a picture.

739
00:45:49,805 --> 00:45:54,726
And it said, ''Wanted''
and ''Have you seen this man?''

740
00:45:55,394 --> 00:45:58,354
I was like, ''Matter of fact,
I have seen him before.''

741
00:45:59,690 --> 00:46:04,402
I replied, ''Rodriguez is my father.
I'm serious.

742
00:46:04,862 --> 00:46:07,655
''Do you really want to know
about my father?

743
00:46:07,698 --> 00:46:11,367
''Sometimes the fantasy
is better left alive.''

744
00:46:11,368 --> 00:46:13,495
I don't know why I said that,
but anyway I did.

745
00:46:13,537 --> 00:46:17,332
And then I gave them e-mail address,
phone numbers,

746
00:46:17,374 --> 00:46:20,710
anything that they wanted to contact me.
And he phoned me.

747
00:46:26,342 --> 00:46:28,384
<i>(Segerman) Well, we'd found out</i>
<i>that Rodriguez was alive.</i>

748
00:46:28,385 --> 00:46:29,844
<i>I'd spoken to Craig.</i>

749
00:46:29,887 --> 00:46:32,680
I came to work and Alex McCrindle,

750
00:46:32,723 --> 00:46:34,724
who was the guy I worked
on the website with said,

751
00:46:34,767 --> 00:46:38,186
''You're not going to believe
what's on the website.''

752
00:46:38,229 --> 00:46:41,898
And on the website was a forum
where people could post messages,

753
00:46:42,024 --> 00:46:43,525
and there was a message that said,

754
00:46:43,567 --> 00:46:46,236
''My name's Eva.
I'm Rodriguez's daughter.''

755
00:46:46,362 --> 00:46:47,737
<i>She'd left a phone number and she said,</i>

756
00:46:47,863 --> 00:46:49,113
<i>''I'd like to speak to someone</i>

757
00:46:49,240 --> 00:46:50,532
<i>in connection with this.''</i>

758
00:46:50,574 --> 00:46:52,784
<i>So that night I phoned her.</i>

759
00:46:52,910 --> 00:46:55,453
I said, ''Hi, I'm Sugar,''
and she said, ''I'm Eva,''

760
00:46:55,579 --> 00:46:58,039
and we had the most
amazing conversation.

761
00:46:58,082 --> 00:47:02,252
She explained to me who her father was,
what he had done, where he had been.

762
00:47:02,378 --> 00:47:05,880
She asked me who I was
and I explained why my name was Sugar

763
00:47:05,923 --> 00:47:08,383
and how I was involved with the website.

764
00:47:08,425 --> 00:47:10,593
<i>And then at the end I said to her,</i>

765
00:47:10,636 --> 00:47:13,054
<i>''This has been the most</i>
<i>amazing thing for me,</i>

766
00:47:13,097 --> 00:47:14,889
<i>''and what would be really great</i>
<i>is if I could,</i>

767
00:47:14,932 --> 00:47:16,766
<i>''at some point, speak to your dad.</i>

768
00:47:16,892 --> 00:47:18,768
<i>''I'd love it if I could</i>
<i>just say hello to him.''</i>

769
00:47:18,811 --> 00:47:21,437
<i>Because, for me,</i>
<i>this was sort of the end of the search</i>

770
00:47:21,480 --> 00:47:23,439
<i>and I just wanted to speak to this man.</i>

771
00:47:23,440 --> 00:47:25,400
And then I went to bed.

772
00:47:25,442 --> 00:47:28,653
And 1:00 in the morning that night,
the phone rang.

773
00:47:29,446 --> 00:47:33,116
And my wife answers it
'cause it was her side of the bed.

774
00:47:33,242 --> 00:47:37,745
And I remember she picked up the phone
and her face just changed.

775
00:47:37,788 --> 00:47:41,958
She had this look of awe.
She said, ''It's him.''

776
00:47:42,084 --> 00:47:44,127
And I was in shock. I'd been sleeping

777
00:47:44,253 --> 00:47:47,297
and I ran into the other room,
into my study,

778
00:47:47,339 --> 00:47:49,841
and I picked up the phone
and she put hers down.

779
00:47:49,967 --> 00:47:52,510
And I said, ''Hello?'' and a voice said...

780
00:47:52,636 --> 00:47:54,470
<i>(Rodriguez's voice on phone)</i>
<i>''Hello, is that Sugar?''</i>

781
00:47:54,471 --> 00:47:58,266
And I knew, I just knew,
because I knew that voice.

782
00:47:58,309 --> 00:48:01,936
I'd heard that voice so many times
on the records, I knew it was him.

783
00:48:01,979 --> 00:48:03,813
I was talking to Rodriguez.

784
00:48:04,648 --> 00:48:08,151
<i>That, for me, was one of</i>
<i>the greatest moments of my life.</i>

